This app is for people who are required to file a 2019 or 2018 tax return.
Can my bank apply my stimulus payment to the negative balance?
“The Cares Act does not prohibit banks from taking part of the stimulus payment to cover a negative balance, a defaulted loan other than a credit card, or overdraft fees.
USAA said it will no longer apply stimulus payments to customer debts after the American Prospect reported that its bank took $3,400 in Cares Act payments from the family of a disabled veteran to offset a debt at the banks.
“For active member deposit accounts, we have paused the recovery of any negative account balance existing at the time their stimulus payment was deposited for a period of 90 days, allowing members access to their full stimulus payment for this time period.